This is a known breaking change in .NET 10 MAUI. Android adopted **edge-to-edge** rendering by default, which makes `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` (and its MAUI wrapper `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize`) no longer work. The fix is to handle **IME window insets** instead.

### 1. `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`

```csharp
using AndroidX.Core.View;

[Activity(/* existing attributes */,
    WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustResize)]   // still needed as a hint
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Listen for keyboard (IME) insets on the root content view
        var content = FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(content, new ImeInsetsListener());
    }

    sealed class ImeInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(
            Android.Views.View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var ime    = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var bars   = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());
            int bottom = Math.Max(ime.Bottom, bars.Bottom);

            view.SetPadding(bars.Left, bars.Top, bars.Right, bottom);
            return WindowInsetsCompat.Consumed;
        }
    }
}
```

### 2. Chat page layout (XAML)

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0"
                    ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}"
                    ItemsUpdatingScrollMode="KeepLastItemInView" />

    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message…"
               HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" Command="{Binding SendCommand}" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

### Why this works

| Old (.NET 9) | New (.NET 10) |
|---|---|
| `AdjustResize` shrinks the window | Window stays full-screen (edge-to-edge) |
| System auto-moves views | You apply bottom padding from `Ime()` insets |

The `ImeInsetsListener` detects the keyboard height and adds matching bottom padding to the root view, pushing your `Grid.Row="1"` input bar above the keyboard.

### iOS

iOS still uses `UIScrollView` auto-adjustment, so this is typically an **Android-only** fix. If you also have issues on iOS, add `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect()` in `Platforms/iOS/AppDelegate.cs` and manage scroll insets manually — but most chat layouts work out of the box on iOS.
